{{Unreferenced|date=December 2006}}
'''''The Golden Hour''''' was an [[ITV]] drama series, first shown in [[2005]].

The series centred on the activities of a specialist medical unit, HEMS (standing for Helicopter Emergency Medical Service) which is based in [[London]], operated by the London Ambulance Service, in dealing with emergency cases. The title refers to [[Golden hour (medicine)|the hour]] which is their critical time for handling emergencies.

The series starred [[Richard Armitage (actor)|Richard Armitage]].
It also starred [[Lorna Fitzgerald]], who plays [[Abi Branning]] in [[EastEnders]].

